 ==== Install Redis 2.0+=====

sudo  apt-get redis

 ==== install node.js, npm, socket.io and redis for node.js ====

Use following instructions
http://www.giantflyingsaucer.com/blog/?p=1688

>install git, just in case

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install git-core
$ sudo apt-get install build-essential openssl libssl-dev

>takes some time to compile

$ git clone http://github.com/ry/node.git && cd node
$ ./configure
$ make
$ sudo make install

>test to see if it is installed

$ node -v

>install curl

$ sudo apt-get install curl

>install the npm (node package manager)

$ curl http://npmjs.org/install.sh | sh

> if you get a permission error, do 

$ sudo chown -R $USER /usr/local

> install socket.io

npm install socket.io

> install redis for node.js

npm install redis
